From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 29 Nov 2025 14:49:26 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] pci: cadence: sky1: Fix ATU/ECAM register layout for CIX Sky1
 SoC

The CIX Sky1 SoC uses a Cadence PCIe IP with vendor-specific register
layout that differs from mainline. This patch fixes the following issues:

ATU Register Layout:
- Change outbound region base from 0x9000 to 0xa000 (AXI_SLAVE + 0x1000)
- Change outbound region stride from 0x20 to 0x80 per region
- Change DESC0 TYPE bits from [3:0] to [28:24]
- Change DESC1 bus/devfn to bits [31:24] and [23:16]
- Add CTRL0 register support with SUPPLY_BUS and SUPPLY_DEV_FN flags
- Change LINKDOWN register from 0x9824 to 0x9004
- Change inbound base to 0xb000 (AXI_MASTER_OFFSET)

ECAM/SBSA Support:
- Add ecam_support_flag to cdns_pcie_rc structure
- Add cdns_pcie_create_region_for_ecam() with SBSA mode enable
- Program TAG_MANAGEMENT, SLAVE_RESP, ROOT_PORT_REQ_ID registers
- Enable LM_HAL_SBSA_CTRL for hardware ECAM translation
- Set up ATU region 0 for ECAM pass-through

Bug Fixes:
- Add guards to preserve cfg_base/reg_base from glue driver setup
- Fix cdns_pci_map_bus to write DESC1/CTRL0 correctly
- Add cdns,no-inbound-bar check to skip inbound BAR setup
- Update outbound region setup to write CTRL0 register

DTS Changes:
- Disable unused PCIe controllers and peripherals for bring-up
- Keep pcie_x4_rc enabled for NVMe boot

Tested on Radxa Orion O6 with NVMe boot from mainline 6.18-rc7.
